.TH "dma_fence_chain_init" 9 "dma_fence_chain_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
dma_fence_chain_init \- initialize a fence chain
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" dma_fence_chain_init
.BI "(struct dma_fence_chain *chain "  ","
.BI "struct dma_fence *prev "  ","
.BI "struct dma_fence *fence "  ","
.BI "uint64_t seqno "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "chain" 12
the chain node to initialize
.IP "prev" 12
the previous fence
.IP "fence" 12
the current fence
.IP "seqno" 12
the sequence number to use for the fence chain
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Initialize a new chain node and either start a new chain or add the node to
the existing chain of the previous fence.
